1. Assessment Phase:
  Conduct a comprehensive audit of existing data sources, formats, and quality.
Engage stakeholders to understand specific business requirements and data usage patterns.

2. Design Phase:
  Develop a data integration plan outlining the connectivity between various systems.
Create a data cleansing strategy specifying techniques and tools for quality improvement.
Design data transformation processes to align with business intelligence goals.

3. Implementation Phase:
  Deploy integration tools and middleware to establish seamless data flow.
Execute data cleansing techniques to rectify identified issues.
Implement transformation processes to convert and enrich raw data.

4. Testing and Validation:
  Conduct thorough testing to ensure the effectiveness of integration, cleansing, and transformation processes.
Validate data quality improvements through before-and-after analyses.
Solicit feedback from end-users to gauge usability and performance.

